{
  "page": "Lord Darklyn (father of Jonquil Darke)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\"><img alt=\"House Darklyn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/50px-House_Darklyn.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/75px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/100px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Lord Darklyn</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\"><img alt=\"House Darklyn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/50px-House_Darklyn.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/75px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/100px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Duskendale\" title=\"Lord of Duskendale\">Lord of Duskendale</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/50_AC\" title=\"50 AC\">50&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/51_AC\" title=\"51 AC\">51&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>At least one son<sup id=\"cite_ref-Son_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Son-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil_Darke\" title=\"Jonquil Darke\">Jonquil Darke</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sons_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Sons of the Dragon\">The Sons of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lord Darklyn</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a> during the reigns of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I</a> and King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/48_AC\" title=\"48 AC\">48&#160;AC</a>, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_Targaryen%27s_uprising\" title=\"Jaehaerys Targaryen&#39;s uprising\">pressed his claim to the throne</a> against his <a href=\"/index.php/Usurper\" title=\"Usurper\">usurping</a> uncle, King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>, and high lords of the realm flocked to his cause. Maegor commanded a score of lesser lords, including Lord Darklyn, to gather at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, but their numbers were few and many soon lost heart. Shortly afterwards, Maegor was found dead upon the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>, and the prince ascended as King Jaehaerys I Targaryen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In the chaos that followed Maegor's death, many lords fled the capital, but Lord Darklyn remained.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Along with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jordan_Towers\" title=\"Jordan Towers\">Jordan Towers</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton_(father_of_Cassella)\" title=\"Lord Staunton (father of Cassella)\">Lord Staunton</a>, he yielded the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> to Prince Jaehaerys, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena</a>, and Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne Targaryen</a>. The three lords were sent to the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_cells\" title=\"Black cells\">black cells</a>, but were eventually pardoned by King Jaehaerys I after surrendering some of their land and sending a son to court to serve as a <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/50_AC\" title=\"50 AC\">50&#160;AC</a>, Lord Darklyn was among the lords who visited Jaehaerys at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. This displeased Jaehaerys' <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rogar_Baratheon\" title=\"Rogar Baratheon\">Rogar Baratheon</a>, who referred to them as the \"lords lickspittle\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Darklyn died that same year or the one after, and he was succeeded as Lord of Duskendale by his son. It is unknown if it was the father or the son who hosted King Jaehaerys and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne Targaryen</a> at Duskendale during their first <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/51_AC\" title=\"51 AC\">51&#160;AC</a>. Lord Darklyn's <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil_Darke\" title=\"Jonquil Darke\">Jonquil Darke</a>, was named the queen's <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_shield\" title=\"Sworn shield\">sworn shield</a> after an <a href=\"/index.php/Assassin\" title=\"Assassin\">assassination</a> attempt on Alysanne failed when the royal couple visited <a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil%27s_Pool\" title=\"Jonquil&#39;s Pool\">Jonquil's Pool</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Darklyn had at least one trueborn son<sup id=\"cite_ref-Son_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Son-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> and a bastard daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil_Darke\" title=\"Jonquil Darke\">Jonquil Darke</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> His relation to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Darklyn\" title=\"Davos Darklyn\">Davos Darklyn</a>, a member of Maegor I's <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Son-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Son_4-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Son_4-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">In <a href=\"/index.php/48_AC\" title=\"48 AC\">48&#160;AC</a>, Lord Darklyn was forced to send a son to court to serve as a <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a> in order to be welcomed back into the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Peace\" title=\"King&#39;s Peace\">King's Peace</a> by King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> By <a href=\"/index.php/51_AC\" title=\"51 AC\">51&#160;AC</a>, Lord Darklyn had died and was succeeded by his son.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is unknown if the new Lord Darklyn and the hostage were the same individual.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Darklyn_(father_of_Jonquil_Darke)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Sons of the Dragon.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Birth, Death and Betrayal Under King Jaehaerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Prince into King - The Ascension of Jaehaerys I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, A Surfeit of Rulers.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"wikitable succession-box noprint\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:small;clear:both;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b> <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Duskendale\" title=\"Lord of Duskendale\">Lord of Duskendale</a> </b><br />?–<a href=\"/index.php/50_AC\" title=\"50 AC\">50</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/51_AC\" title=\"51 AC\">51&#160;AC</a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b><div style=\"font-size:90%\">Next known title holder:</div><b><a href=\"/index.php/Gunthor_Darklyn\" title=\"Gunthor Darklyn\">Gunthor Darklyn</a> </b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403133247\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.108 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.318 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1727/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 13227/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 11379/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3587/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 15/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 6079/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.59 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  299.216      1 -total\n 87.34%  261.330      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 86.75%  259.555      1 Template:Infobox\n 13.93%   41.693     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  7.32%   21.898      8 Template:Date\n  6.84%   20.470     11 Template:Ref\n  4.29%   12.834     11 Template:Ref/core\n  3.62%   10.839      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  3.20%    9.561      1 Template:S-ttl\n  2.91%    8.699      1 Template:Refn\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:27505-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403133247 and revision id 317373\n -->\n",
